rComments: He is super nice and very knowledgable. If you did badly on a test you could go talk to him and he would most likely raise your score. Also he teaches at the University of Colorado at Boulder now.

Nakassis is a really great lecturer, very clear and interesting. His tests were pretty easy, always give opinions (ie. answer 15 out of 20 IDs or 2 out 3 short answer ). Give lots of feedback for the final essay.  Would take a course with him again, if  I have the chance.

Nakassis is a great professor, he is really funny and witty. Makes us laugh almost every class. His course work is simple and easy, no surprises. He is really easy to approach, always helps you out if you need it. I look forward to having him again!

Awesome class! He's a little forgetful at points, but is willing to find the answer to any questions asked.  Lectures are a must! He's funny and witty, which makes the material that much more appealing. (annnnd he's hot...)
Super clever, witty, and funny. A pleasure to listen to in lecture (and an absolute pleasure to look at). Extremely approachable.

Very approachable and friendly, has a great sense of humour. Fair marker, though the constructive criticism was lacking a bit (maybe it's just that I did very well in the class?) One of those profs that I would love to have coffee with and pick their brain.
